reviewText: TT IS A BAD BAD DAD WESTERN, IF NOT A WHOLE LOT WORSE. ACTUALLY WORSE THAN WORSE. AWKWARD AND MEANINGLESS.
Did not watch all of it, very bad acting.  Looks like a home made movie?  Should have been R with language.

This is an action packed Western, with less swearing, and better acting.  Bob Handigan plays a good role in this movie, and after seeing it--I know you won't be disappointed. This movie is a cross between HIGH NOON and TOMBSTONE.

claims to be another classic ... well it aint going to happen...
actors.. they aint.. sound quality isn't there lacks a lot of luster ..
the director must have been asleep during the making of the picture... if u want to call it that ... this is  a film ... that should not have been made ..save ur money .. there is better films out there than this....

This is the worst movie I have ever seen. It is nothing more than a home movie with a family of amateurs as the cast. The acting is horrible - totally unbelievable. the plot is not much better. I fast forwarded through most of it to see if there was anything worth watching.
Do not waste your money on this movie.

After watching half of it I did turn it OFF.
I have one word for it as what Leonard Maltin says in his classification's
for the bottom of the barrel movies-He does not give them even one star, It is not worth even one star from me.
Wasted my time and money.

Considering that this is a very small time production it is not bad, not great but not bad.  Some of the dialog is cheesy as well as the acting.  But all in all not a bad movie.  Also, I know the star Bob Handigan, we go way back, Bob would be so good in a comedy.  I had a hard time taking him serious, cause he rarely is.  It is worth a watch.

I was very impressed with the final edit done by Barnholtz Entertainment.  The film is now down to 93 minutes and flows much faster now.  Also check out this review by Fitz at blogcritics.org:

This is an olde fashioned horse opera set in a cardboard, plywood, movie set painted out to be real with a certain videoographic backdrop attempting to fool the viewer into thinking ~ this is authentic! When it is painfully obvious this was a low budget film with unknown actors!

I normally don't review movies. I watch pretty much anything. This one I couldn't figure out if it was meant to be deliberately bad or not. The acting was very melodramatic. The dialog was very wooden and poor. The music was over the top.  I've seen high school plays much better than this. Bad? Almost bad enough to be funny good. Fortunately an hour into the movie they started using split screens that way the pain was shortened. Too bad they didn't use it all the way to the end. Im just curious where they got the actors? Did they get paid?

If you like the old time westerns, you will not like this. It was poorly written in my opinion. It looks like it was done by high school students trying to get extra credit! The acting just wasn't believable.  My husband and I could not watch the whole movie. It was boring
I couldn't handle the slow, poorly acted story of this movie.  I made it through 1/2 of it before I called it quits.  Normally, I persevere through but I just couldn't stomach this one.
Tried to watch it but couldn't get past the first 5 minutes. Even fast forwarded to see if it would get better - it didn't. Horrible acting and looks like it was shot with home video equipment.

I agree with the other reviewers that the acting was elementary, like grade school acting.  Very wooden in delivery.  The other criticism that I have is the dialog.  The only good thing about this movie are 1) makes your appreciate good acting, and 2) good screen play, two thing that this movie lacks.

Couldn't get past the first 20 minutes due to some of the worst acting and directing I think I've ever seen.  No wonder I never heard of this movie (and I see most of the good movies at the theatre when they come out).

I would classify this movie as being barely "ok'.  I was tempted a couple of times to just cut it off and do something else, but continued watching it in hopes that it would improve.  The acting is basically at an amateur level.

This is a good western because it has all the earmarks of adventure, violence and fun.  The sheriff is not someone you want to fool with and it has a twist in the end which you will like.  Thanks for having a bunch of westerns.

Good storyline. But very predictable. Poorly acted. If you want to see a good western watch Open Range. One of the best modern Westerns I've ever seen.
